{"title":"Got a Roomba? Clean these filthy components right now","link":"https://www.techhive.com/article/3606392/how-to-clean-a-roomba-charging-contacts-and-cliff-sensors.html#tk.rss_all","date":1612954800000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><section role=\"main\" id=\"page-wrapper\"><article itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Article\"><meta itemprop=\"keywords\" content=\"vaccuums, smart appliances \"><header><section><h3 itemprop=\"description\">If your Roomba is having trouble docking or has slowed to a crawl, a good scrub might make things right.</h3></section><div><p>Senior Writer, <span itemprop=\"publisher\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/Organization\"><span itemprop=\"name\">TechHive</span><meta itemprop=\"url\" content=\"https://www.techhive.com\"><meta itemprop=\"logo\" content=\"https://alt.idgesg.net/images/furniture/techhive/TH_logo_300x300.png\"></span><span>|</span> <span itemprop=\"datePublished\" content=\"2021-02-10T03:00-0800\"><span>Feb 10, 2021 3:00 am PST</span></span></p></div></header><div><div><figure itemprop=\"image\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/ImageObject\"><meta itemprop=\"representativeOfPage\" content=\"1\"><meta itemprop=\"height\" content=\"801\"><meta itemprop=\"width\" content=\"1200\"><meta itemprop=\"url\" content=\"https://images.idgesg.net/images/article/2021/02/roomba-675-wipe-off-cliff-sensor-100876475-large.jpg\"><img data-original=\"https://images.idgesg.net/images/article/2021/02/roomba-675-wipe-off-cliff-sensor-100876475-large.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"roomba 675 wipe off cliff sensor\" itemprop=\"contentUrl\" onload=\"try {performance.clearMarks('mark_primary_img_rendered'); performance.mark('mark_primary_img_rendered');}catch(e) {console.log('Error saving performance mark -- this function may not be supported in this browser');}\" src=\"https://images.idgesg.net/images/article/2021/02/roomba-675-wipe-off-cliff-sensor-100876475-large.jpg\"><figcaption kioskedhash_production=\"11429_6a66d5970fafad677b176faab70f7567\" data-kiosked-context-name=\"kskdUIContext_01eydqs9tmprrep0mrsgzxsdhk\"><span itemprop=\"copyrightHolder\">Ben Patterson/IDG</span></figcaption></figure></div></div><section><div id=\"drr-container\" itemprop=\"articleBody\"><p dir=\"ltr\">I thought I’d been doing a good job keeping my <a href=\"http://buy.geni.us/Proxy.ashx?TSID=14157&amp;GR_URL=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB07DL4QY5V%2F%3Fascsubtag%3DUS-003-3606392-000-000000-web-20\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-product-name=\"iRobot Roomba 675\" data-vars-product-name=\"iRobot Roomba 675\" data-vars-outbound-link=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B07DL4QY5V/\" data-product-id=\"000000\" data-vars-product-id=\"000000\" data-bkmfr=\"iRobot\" data-vars-bkmfr=\"iRobot\" data-bkvndr=\"Amazon\" data-vars-bkvndr=\"Amazon\">iRobot Roomba 675</a><a href=\"#\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> clean, carefully pulling clumps of hair off its brushes and wheels and emptying its bin after every cleaning. Little did I know that dust and gunk were building up in places where I wasn’t even looking.</p><p dir=\"ltr\">First, consider the metal charging contacts on the Roomba’s base station. When was the last time you gave them a close look—or looked at them at all, for that matter?</p><p dir=\"ltr\">I sure hadn’t, but when I did, I saw that instead of being completely silver, one of the two contacts had a rust-colored ring around it, while the other was almost completely discolored.</p><figure kioskedhash_production=\"11429_36c80225c7d473abd7fd1d641877a160\" data-kiosked-context-name=\"kskdUIContext_01eydqs9tmprrep0mrsgzxsdhk\"><a href=\"https://images.idgesg.net/images/article/2021/02/roomba-675-dirty-charging-contact-100876473-orig.jpeg\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"<div class='credit'>Ben Patterson/IDG</div>\n<p>This dirty Roomba charging contact used to be competely silver.</p>\n\"><img alt=\"roomba 675 dirty charging contact\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-imageid=\"100876473\" data-license=\"IDG\" data-original=\"https://images.idgesg.net/images/article/2021/02/roomba-675-dirty-charging-contact-100876473-large.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.idgesg.net/images/article/2021/02/roomba-675-dirty-charging-contact-100876473-large.jpg\"></a><small>Ben Patterson/IDG</small><figcaption><p>This dirty Roomba charging contact used to be competely silver.</p></figcaption></figure><p dir=\"ltr\">Having gunked-up charging contacts on your Roomba base station isn’t just a cosmetic issue. At some point, those contacts will get so dirty that your Roomba will have a tough time docking and charging, and you might find yourself with a near-dead Roomba the next time you want to clean your floors.</p><div><p><img onclick=\"jwplayer('bottomRightPlayer').remove(); this.style.display = 'none';\" id=\"jw-standalone-close-button\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\"></p></div><p dir=\"ltr\">Also, have you noticed that your Roomba has been moving slowly or erratic lately? If the Roomba’s IR-enabled cliff sensors get too dusty and dirty, they’ll block the IR beam that’s supposed to reflect back, which means the vacuum might think that it’s continually approaching a wall or about to tumble down the stairs.</p><figure kioskedhash_production=\"11429_163f5b6d62b552be1ffee8424826b2ad\" data-kiosked-context-name=\"kskdUIContext_01eydqs9tmprrep0mrsgzxsdhk\"><a href=\"https://images.idgesg.net/images/article/2021/02/roomba-675-dirty-cliff-sensor-100876474-orig.jpeg\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"<div class='credit'>Ben Patterson/IDG</div>\n<p>Guh-<em>ross!</em></p>\n\"><img alt=\"roomba 675 dirty cliff sensor\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-imageid=\"100876474\" data-license=\"IDG\" data-original=\"https://images.idgesg.net/images/article/2021/02/roomba-675-dirty-cliff-sensor-100876474-large.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.idgesg.net/images/article/2021/02/roomba-675-dirty-cliff-sensor-100876474-large.jpg\"></a><small>Ben Patterson/IDG</small><figcaption><p>Guh-<em>ross!</em></p></figcaption></figure><p dir=\"ltr\">I admit that I’d never bothered to look closely at my Roomba’s cliff sensors until very recently, and when I did … <em>yuck</em>. One of the sensors was almost completely covered in dirt, while the other three were clearly due for a wipe-down.</p><div data-tracking-category=\"In-article TOC\"><legend>Table of Contents <i></i></legend><ul><li data-pagenum=\"1\" data-tocnum=\"1\"><a href=\"#toc-1\">How to clean your Roomba’s charging contacts</a></li><li data-pagenum=\"1\" data-tocnum=\"2\"><a href=\"#toc-2\">How to clean your Roomba’s IR sensors</a></li></ul><p>Show More <i></i></p></div><h2 dir=\"ltr\" id=\"toc-1\">How to clean your Roomba’s charging contacts</h2><p dir=\"ltr\">Roomba manufacturer iRobot recommends regularly cleaning your vacuum’s charging contacts and cliff sensors with a damp melamine foam. If you’re wondering what melamine foam is (I know I was), just think <a href=\"http://buy.geni.us/Proxy.ashx?TSID=14157&amp;GR_URL=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fdp%2FB08492Q875%3Fascsubtag%3DUS-003-3606392-000-000000-web-20\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-product-name=\"Mr. Clean’s Magic Eraser\" data-vars-product-name=\"Mr. Clean’s Magic Eraser\" data-vars-outbound-link=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B08492Q875\" data-product-id=\"000000\" data-vars-product-id=\"000000\" data-bkmfr=\"Mr. Clean\" data-vars-bkmfr=\"Mr. Clean\" data-bkvndr=\"Amazon\" data-vars-bkvndr=\"Amazon\">Mr. Clean’s Magic Eraser</a><a href=\"#\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a> (or <a href=\"http://buy.geni.us/Proxy.ashx?TSID=14157&amp;GR_URL=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2Fs%3Fk%3Dmelamine%2Bfoam%26ascsubtag%3DUS-003-3606392-000-000000-web-20\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" data-product-name=\"Generic melamine foam\" data-vars-product-name=\"Generic melamine foam\" data-vars-outbound-link=\"https://www.amazon.com/s?k=melamine+foam\" data-product-id=\"000000\" data-vars-product-id=\"000000\" data-bkmfr=\"Various\" data-vars-bkmfr=\"Various\" data-bkvndr=\"Amazon\" data-vars-bkvndr=\"Amazon\">one of these brands</a><a href=\"#\" rel=\"nofollow\"></a>).</p><figure><a href=\"https://images.idgesg.net/images/article/2021/02/roomba-675-clean-charging-contact-100876472-orig.jpeg\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"<div class='credit'>Ben Patterson/IDG</div>\n<p>You’ll need to apply a fair amount of elbow grease to clean the charging contacts on your Roomba’s home base.</p>\n\"><img alt=\"roomba 675 clean charging contact\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-imageid=\"100876472\" data-license=\"IDG\" data-original=\"https://images.idgesg.net/images/article/2021/02/roomba-675-clean-charging-contact-100876472-large.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.idgesg.net/images/article/2021/02/roomba-675-clean-charging-contact-100876472-large.jpg\"></a><small>Ben Patterson/IDG</small><figcaption><p>You’ll need to apply a fair amount of elbow grease to clean the charging contacts on your Roomba’s home base.</p></figcaption></figure><p dir=\"ltr\">I ran my Magic Eraser under the kitchen faucet, wrung it out, then began polishing the charging contacts on my Roomba’s home base. It took a surprisingly amount of elbow grease to rub the gunk off, but eventually the silver began shining through again. Also, don’t forget to clean the corresponding contacts on the underside of the Roomba itself.</p><div><p>Today's Best Tech Deals</p><p>Picked by TechHive's Editors</p></div><div><p>Top Deals On Great Products</p><p>Picked by Techconnect's Editors</p></div><h2 dir=\"ltr\" id=\"toc-2\">How to clean your Roomba’s IR sensors</h2><p dir=\"ltr\">Cleaning the cliff sensors was much easier. All you’re doing basically is wiping the dirt of the clear plastic windows that guard the IR lenses, and while I didn’t get them perfectly clean, at least they’re no longer coated with dust.</p><figure><a href=\"https://images.idgesg.net/images/article/2021/02/roomba-675-clean-cliff-sensor-100876471-orig.jpeg\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"<div class='credit'>Ben Patterson/IDG</div>\n<p>This is what the cliff sensors on your Roomba should look like.</p>\n\"><img alt=\"roomba 675 clean cliff sensor\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-imageid=\"100876471\" data-license=\"IDG\" data-original=\"https://images.idgesg.net/images/article/2021/02/roomba-675-clean-cliff-sensor-100876471-large.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.idgesg.net/images/article/2021/02/roomba-675-clean-cliff-sensor-100876471-large.jpg\"></a><small>Ben Patterson/IDG</small><figcaption><p>This is what the cliff sensors on your Roomba should look like.</p></figcaption></figure><p dir=\"ltr\">Of course, some Roomba models have more cliff sensors than others, and they might be located in different places. <a href=\"https://homesupport.irobot.com/app/answers/detail/a_id/525/~/how-do-i-clean-roomba%C2%AE-cliff-sensors%3F\" rel=\"nofollow\">Check out these diagrams from iRobot’s support site</a> for the details on your particular Roomba.</p><div><p>Note: When you purchase something after clicking links in our articles, we may earn a small commission. Read our <a href=\"https://www.techhive.com/about/affiliates.html\">affiliate link policy</a> for more details.</p></div></div><div><p>Ben has been writing about technology and consumer electronics for more than 20 years. A PCWorld contributor since 2014, Ben joined TechHive in 2019, where he covers smart home and home entertainment products.</p></div></section></article></section></div>","author":"Ben Patterson","siteTitle":"Macworld","siteHash":"37e84dd5a21fa961d6d6630e269546024dbb7741b2e2fadbe74f47383c70dfbb","entryHash":"44f605c759d7526037f573bfcdfd2a7f546842172f1685b15abc04c2df920b1f","category":"Apple"}